oduction that changed the way Americans consumed and assimilated food. Asking his readers to think about mapping the processes and locations of digestion, Nicholas Bauch moves outward from the stomach to the sanitarium and through the landscape, clarifying the relationship between food, body, and environment at a crucial moment in the emergence of American health food sensibilities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh  abattle creek sanitarium.  abiotechnology.  acalifornia studies in food.  acereal.  adigestion research.  adigestion.  adigestive research.  adigestive tract.  afood and agriculture.  afood and nutrition.  afood innovation.  afood mapping.  afood processing.  afood science.  afood studies.  afood technology.  afood.  agastrology.  agut health.  akellogg company.  akellogg.  amaking food digestible.  amaking food nutritious.  amaking food.  anutrition research.  anutritionists.  ascientists.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106675470 cprintz978052028579840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096118040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520961180423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520961180/original  a978-3-11-066754-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY